HEADWORD: Pleuropneumonia
<hw>Pleu`ro*pneu*mo"ni*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pleuro-</ets> + <ets>pneumonia</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Inflammation of the pleura and lungs; a
combination of pleurisy and pneumonia, esp. a kind of contagions and
fatal lung plague of cattle.</def>⟦br⟧
